          ... brought forward some misunderstanding. I didn't mean to discredit all of these newer bands. I don't like any of the musicians and bands nearly as much as these new groups coming out; however, my point was in order to be great you need to be timeless. If after 10 years or 20 years you fade away into the extremely rare radio request on the oldies station then you were good, but you weren't great. <br /><br />Music speaks to everyone. Every song out there means something to someone, but my interpretation of "greatest musicians ever" automatically makes me think of your beetles or bob marley and the wailers or even beetoven. I still think there has to be a certain noticable impact generated to seperate a musician from good and great. <br />
